We've noticed that some miners are optimizing their Subtensor instance, which is completely understandable and recommended (and if you do, highly recommended to share with subtensor team in order to improve the ecosystem overall). We aim to build the best possible bootnodes for our Subvortex. However, choosing the same provider doesn't necessarily make a difference if you're not maximizing your infrastructure or the Subtensor itself.

We monitor the network regularly and implement improvements to ensure fair competition among miners/validators in this subnet. Meanwhile, if you can not optimize further on your end, aim to do the minimum to stay competitive. Please note that seats are limited, and only the best will secure their positions.

**Subnet 7 Subvortex Community Committee**  @subvortex ・7 

**Background**
The Subvortex community has proven many times to be one of the best communities for miners, validators and owners to collaborate and create a great environment where even though everyone is trying to be that top miner, we still help each other troubleshoot problems, save miners from attacks and share our ideas and thoughts on what can make this subnet even better!

**What is this committee?**
Members of the community that are interested (on an optional and voluntary basis) can join the committee to represent the miners in discussions with the SubVortex team. Some items this committee can discuss include:
•    Testing of new implementations. This would mostly be done in testnet and some things that can be done in mainnet (will not put miners at risk).
•    Feedback on the current state of mining. Are there issues or things that are not working well? 
•    Ideas and feedback for the future roadmap. This can include discussing ideas the SubVortex team has, ideas the committee members have and brainstorming new ideas.
•    Members are encouraged to help answer questions in our community and also bring back questions that may be of concern. SubVortex members will continue to be active in our channel and this will not change.

**What this committee is not.**
•    This is not an alpha group where committee members will receive insights that give them an advantage over other miners.
•    This is not for private troubleshooting of problems people are experiencing (but we can discuss issues that are or may be relevant to the community overall).

**Next steps**
If you’re interested in being part of the committee, please express your interest on here and tag me or you can DM me. This is the first community committee on any subnet that I’m aware of, so I’m not sure what the level of interest will be. I am leaning towards having either 5 or so members to start and potentially expanding as needed. If you are interested, please be prepared to provide the following information:
•    Why do you want to be part of the group?
•    What is your background (what technical expertise or other skills do you have? We don’t need just purely technical experts; this is more to understand the backgrounds of our members.)
•    Are you part of a mining group? If so, who are the other members of the group?
•    How many keys/miners are you and/or your group currently running?
